[normal]Malcolm Gammie:[bold] There is no bright line, in many respects, between LLPs, partnerships, ordinary partnerships, companies and so on.  Within large organisations you can have a combination of all these different entities to create different structures.  You can have a limited liability partnership whose members may all be corporates, maybe a mixture of individuals and corporates.  They may be ordinary limited partnerships under the 1907
